  "prompt": "What is the curved surface area of a hemisphere?",
  "response": "The curved surface area of a hemisphere can be calculated using the formula:\n\n\\[ A = 2\\pi r^2 \\]\n\nwhere \\( r \\) is the radius of the hemisphere.\n\nFor example, if the radius (r) is 3 units, then the curved surface area would be:\n\n\\[ A = 2\\pi (3)^2 = 2\\pi \\cdot 9 = 18\\pi \\]\n\nSo, the curved surface area of a hemisphere with radius 3 units is \\( 18\\pi \\) square units.",
